13. The method for performing a dimensional inspection of a fabricated composite part (9) according to claim 9, wherein:
said fabricated composite part (9) is an aircraft wing cover (9) comprising a skin (5) and a plurality of stringers (7);
the distribution of said points (Iij, Oij) is arranged for providing positional information for calculating at least the deviations of one or more of the following parameters:
skin thickness along the aircraft wing cover sections where the ribs will be attached;
web height of the stringers along the aircraft wing cover sections where the ribs will be attached;
foot height of the stringers along the aircraft wing cover sections where the ribs will be attached.

